ations, and demonstrate that people in central Africa are currently infected with SFV. Contact with non-human primates, such as happens during hunting and butchering, can play a part in the emergence of human retroviruses and the reduction of primate bushmeat hunting has the potential to decrease the frequency of disease emergence.</p>", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Wolfe, Nathan D.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Switzer, William M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Carr, Jean K.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Bhullar, Vinod B.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Shanmugam, Vedapuri", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Tamoufe, Ubald", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Prosser, A. Tassy", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Torimiro, Judith N.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Wright, Anthony", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Mpoudi-Ngole, Eitel", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "McCutchan, Francine E.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Birx, Deborah L.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Folks, Thomas M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Burke, Donald S.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Heneine, Walid", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/b2b1832600ca6f0291ac796db09d57c6", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/42d760efa0fa82d9efa02e294a6ff592e26f71d0019f3bbfe4c96d473b09b23b", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/SLHDRGAF", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/SLHDRGAF", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/da2383ff74c382cf17ef4aa3aaec3ada!/b226142-230435", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/ce1e7618f237ff56e74d51f496e811a3", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url